    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen I want to go to other directory path it won't let me proceed to that path. There is just a flicker of inside that directory and bump me out.\n\nSometimes it won't load to your choice of directory and will open into your home directory instead.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim . || :Ex (if inside file)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nto open other directory inside netrw\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0 fc7e5cf\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ndont have vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu lts 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.13.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nvia extraction of tar folder and symlinking it to /usr/local/bin/nvim",
